we're gonna murder you.

14:30.070 --> 14:32.072
Beat it!

14:32.072 --> 14:34.107
( crowd laughs )

14:36.543 --> 14:39.846
- Are you okay, Zack?
- I...yeah, I guess.

14:39.879 --> 14:43.850
Wow, Kristy,
you're one very strong woman.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.519
Yeah, it's lucky for you
she was here, huh, Morris?

14:47.153 --> 14:49.222
Yeah, lucky me.

14:54.594 --> 14:58.331
<i>* KKTY... Bayside *</i>

14:58.365 --> 15:01.601
This is Jessica Spano
for "Spano Speaks."

15:01.634 --> 15:04.471
Recently I gave an editorial
supporting a girl's right

15:04.504 --> 15:06.639
to wrestle on a guys' team.

15:06.673 --> 15:09.542
Boy, was I ever wrong.

15:09.576 --> 15:12.312
Girls have absolutely
no business wrestling guys.

15:12.345 --> 15:14.647
The poor dears could get hurt.

15:14.681 --> 15:18.918
In conclusion, keep your hands
off our men, Kristy.

15:22.956 --> 15:26.059
What was that all about?
I thought you
were all for Kristy.

15:26.059 --> 15:28.595
I know you are.

15:28.628 --> 15:30.063
What's that supposed to mean?

15:30.063 --> 15:33.433
"Oh, Slater, you're so strong.
Hold me tighter."

15:35.769 --> 15:39.372
So that's what
this is all about.
You're jealous.

15:39.406 --> 15:41.708
Come on,
I was just helping a teammate.

15:41.741 --> 15:44.844
Oh yeah?
When was the last time
you held Rodriguez like that?

15:47.080 --> 15:50.850
Why would I want a girl like
Kristy when I can have
a nut-cake like you?

15:53.086 --> 15:56.456
Don't try flattering me,
it won't get you anywhere.

15:58.425 --> 15:59.726
Men!

15:59.759 --> 16:01.061
Chicks!

16:04.731 --> 16:07.867
I can't believe it.
Jessie was my
biggest supporter.

16:07.901 --> 16:09.502
Why would
she say those things?

16:09.536 --> 16:11.304
Maybe she's having a bad day.

16:11.338 --> 16:13.073
That's not it,
her hair's too tight.

16:13.106 --> 16:16.042
I told her not
to wear barrettes
while the moon was full.

16:16.543 --> 16:17.477
What?

16:17.510 --> 16:20.313
It's the gravitational pull
on the follicles.

16:20.347 --> 16:22.449
She was a helpless victim
of nature.

16:24.517 --> 16:27.053
- Hi, Kristy.
- I'm glad you're here.
Did you hear...

16:27.087 --> 16:29.422
Kristy, I can't go
to the movies
with you tonight.

16:29.456 --> 16:31.791
I have to... study.

16:31.825 --> 16:35.562
- Both: Study?!
- Another
casualty of the moon.

16:35.595 --> 16:37.697
I'd better get home
before it gets dark.

16:41.434 --> 16:44.471
Okay,
Zack, why don't we just go
to the movies tomorrow night?

16:45.438 --> 16:48.975
Kristy, it isn't that.
I just...

16:49.075 --> 16:51.544
I just don't think we should
see each other anymore.

16:51.578 --> 16:53.480
It's not working
out between us.

16:54.080 --> 16:55.882
Oh.

16:55.915 --> 16:58.485
Does this have anything to do
with what
happened on our date?

16:58.518 --> 17:02.022
- Well...
- What a great day.

17:02.022 --> 17:04.590
First Jessie wants me off
the wrestling team

17:04.624 --> 17:08.328
and now you can't handle
going out with
a girl wrestler.

17:08.361 --> 17:12.464
I'm gonna make you both happy,
I'm quitting the team.

17:17.103 --> 17:19.406
I would feel the same
even if she wasn't trying

17:19.439 --> 17:22.041
- to wrestle my
man away from me.
- Your man?

17:22.041 --> 17:24.544
Kristy doesn't like Slater,
she likes me.

17:24.577 --> 17:26.880
Ha, ha, ha,
I could see right through it.

17:26.913 --> 17:30.450
- I knew she liked Slater.
- Jessie, read my lips,

17:30.483 --> 17:33.386
Kristy likes me, not Slater.

17:33.420 --> 17:35.889
But Lisa said
Kristy was going out
with a school hunk.

17:35.922 --> 17:38.491
And what do I look like?
A bologna sandwich?

17:39.893 --> 17:42.095
Oops.
What have I done?

17:42.128 --> 17:44.064
Yeah, what have we done?

17:44.064 --> 17:46.866
I was a jealous,
possessive fool.

17:46.900 --> 17:49.135
And I was a fool too,
as usual.

17:49.936 --> 17:51.971
Well, we blew it.

17:52.072 --> 17:54.741
We can't let
her quit the team.
I'll go talk to her.

17:54.774 --> 17:57.911
No,
no, no, you've talked enough.
I'll go talk to her.

17:57.944 --> 18:00.013
Let's hope she doesn't
body slam me.

18:03.016 --> 18:04.684
Leave me alone, Zack.

18:04.718 --> 18:06.920
I told you,
I don't want to talk to you.

18:07.754 --> 18:10.156
Then I'm coming in.

18:10.190 --> 18:11.725
You better get out of here.

18:11.758 --> 18:13.560
If Belding catches you,
you're gonna get suspended.

18:13.593 --> 18:17.731
- I don't care.
I have to talk to you.
- It's a free country, talk.

18:19.065 --> 18:21.601
Kristy, this isn't
easy for me to say,

18:21.634 --> 18:24.938
but I was embarrassed when
you wouldn't let me fight
the guy at The Max.

18:25.038 --> 18:26.539
So?

18:26.573 --> 18:29.075
So the point is a guy
should protect the girl.

18:29.109 --> 18:31.745
I couldn't handle it
when you had to protect me.

18:31.778 --> 18:35.181
- I didn't mean
to embarrass you.
- I know that.

18:35.215 --> 18:39.219
Kristy, you love wrestling.
Don't quit the team
over a jerk like me.

18:40.153 --> 18:41.688
Do you really mean it?

18:42.088 --> 18:44.524
Jerk's honor.

18:44.557 --> 18:45.825
Will you ever forgive me?

18:46.593 --> 18:48.728
On one condition...

18:48.762 --> 18:50.797
if you take me
to the movies tomorrow night.

18:50.830 --> 18:52.499
I'd be afraid not to.

19:01.007 --> 19:03.810
Okay, sports fans,
this should be
a great contest.

19:03.843 --> 19:05.845
Briggs and Slater
are both undefeated.

19:05.879 --> 19:08.048
And they've never
lost either, Zack.

19:09.883 --> 19:11.818
Ready? Okay!

19:11.851 --> 19:15.689
Here comes Slater, he's got
guts! Slam down Valley!
Kick their butts!

19:19.092 --> 19:22.796
Let me tell you, this promises
to be a long, grueling match.

19:22.829 --> 19:24.731
Wrestlers ready!

19:25.632 --> 19:27.067
( whistle blows )

19:30.236 --> 19:31.905
( whistle blows )

19:33.540 --> 19:36.209
Yes, yes, and Slater wins
in record time.

19:36.242 --> 19:40.046
Bayside and Valley are tied,
three matches apiece,
with one to go.

19:40.080 --> 19:41.815
Zack:
Tension is mounting.

19:41.848 --> 19:44.617
This match will determine
the winner of the meet.

19:44.651 --> 19:46.720
Will it be Valley's
Skipper Skulnick?

19:46.753 --> 19:49.856
Or Bayside's first female
wrestler in league history,
Kristy Barnes?

19:49.889 --> 19:51.791
I think so, Zack.

19:53.660 --> 19:55.662
All right, Kristy,
it's up to you now.

19:55.695 --> 19:58.631
If you get into trouble
just remember
what I taught you.

19:58.665 --> 20:00.233
All right.

20:00.266 --> 20:05.005
Hey, Kristy, I'm sorry,
I was wrong about you.

20:05.038 --> 20:07.741
- And you too.
- It's okay, Mama.

20:07.774 --> 20:09.642
I'm used to you by now.

20:12.579 --> 20:15.048
All right,
all right, here we go.

20:15.081 --> 20:17.250
One, two, three, Tigers!

20:18.184 --> 20:21.254
Wrestlers... take your places!

20:23.656 --> 20:25.592
Places! Ready!

20:27.394 --> 20:30.764
( whistle blows,
crowd cheering )

20:30.797 --> 20:33.233
Skulnick and Barnes
are circling each other.

20:33.266 --> 20:35.335
( crowd cheering )

20:38.238 --> 20:41.641
Zack: Oh, no, Skulnick
has Barnes in a Full Nelson.

20:41.675 --> 20:44.944
- She's in trouble.
- Come on,
Kristy, you can do it.

20:44.978 --> 20:48.314
- Fight him, Kristy!
- Yeah, yeah!

20:48.348 --> 20:51.017
Skulnick is forcing Kristy
to the mat.

20:52.786 --> 20:54.821
Do something, Zack.

20:54.854 --> 20:56.856
Kristy, use the hold
you used at The Max.

20:56.890 --> 20:58.925
( cheering continues )

21:07.701 --> 21:09.769
( whistle blows )

21:17.744 --> 21:20.213
All right!

21:20.246 --> 21:23.350
Kristy, how does it feel
to make league history?

21:23.383 --> 21:25.618
- Great!
- ( Zack groans )

21:30.090 --> 21:32.125
Ladies and gentlemen,
that was Kristy Barnes,

21:32.158 --> 21:34.994
our new star wrestler
and also my date for tonight.

21:35.095 --> 21:37.864
and if anyone has
a problem with that,
she'll beat you up.

21:46.172 --> 21:48.742
( instrumental
theme music playing )
